It underlines the importance of controlling the presence of bats before proceeding with maintenance work on the estates, since the unintentional destruction of a single flock can kill up to 400 females and young, which can lead to the extinction of the entire local population.
Bats are under protection —killing, harassing, or disturbing them, as well as destroying their beams, is illegal.
Elisabeth Ferrell, a Scottish Bat Conservation Trust officer, encouraged the public to provide assistance.
She said: “We still have a lot to learn about our bats, and for many species, we don’t even know how their populations are coping.”
