Foreign Minister Says Syria Is 'Ready' for Refugees to Return
The government says Syria is ready for the voluntary return of refugees, and asks for help to rebuild a country devastated by more than seven years of war.
In his address to the UN General Assembly, Syrian Foreign Minister Walid al-Moualem said conditions in the country are improving.
“The situation in our territory is now more stable and safe thanks to progress in the fight against terrorism,” he said.
In an effort to restore normality, the government is constantly rebuilding areas destroyed by terrorists.
All conditions have already been met so that refugees who have had to leave the country due to terrorism and unilateral economic developments aimed at their daily lives and livelihoods can voluntarily return to it.
The United Nations estimates that more than 5.5 million Syrians have left Syria since the start of the war in 2011.
The other six million people who still live there are in need of humanitarian aid.
Al-Moualem said the Syrian regime would gladly accept assistance to rebuild the destroyed country.
However, he stressed that he would not accept aid conditioned or offered by the countries that sponsored the rebellion.
Europe seals victory at the Ryder Cup in Paris
The European team won the 2018 Ryder Cup, defeating the US team with a score of 16.5 to 10.5 on the Le Golf National in the suburbs of Paris.
On European soil, the United States has lost for the sixth time in a row and has not won the Ryder Cup in Europe since 1993.
Europe regained the trophy when under the leadership of the Danish captain, Thomas Bjorn, scored 14.5 points, which were needed to defeat the United States.
The American star, Phil Mickelson, who did not go too well for most of the tournament, hit the ball from the base straight into the water at the 16th hole PAR3, thus giving the match to Francesco Molinari.
The Italian golfer Molinari shined through all rounds and became one of four players who, since 1979, when this tournament was held for the first time in the current format, managed to get a 5-0-0 score.
The American Jordan Spieth was eliminated with a score of 5&4 by the lowest ranked player from Europe, Thorbjorna Olesena from Denmark.
Dustin Johnson, who holds the top position in the world rankings, lost two holes before the last hole to Englishman Ian Poulter, for whom it was perhaps the last Ryder Cup tournament.
The European with the largest number of wins in the Ryder Cup was the Spaniard Sergio Garcia, who has already participated in eight such tournaments and scored 25.5 points in his career.
“I usually don’t cry, but today I can’t stop.
